page.title: 16AROUND AND ABOUT LYNEHAM
page.content: I SAW A THATCHED COTTAGE, IT'S NAME IS "TUDOR COTTAGE".IT HAS BLACK PIECES OF WOOD ON IT AND THREE CHIMNEYS. LAURA CLEMENTS 6YRS SIX OF US WENT TO THE GARAGE IN LYNEHAM AND THERE WERE 45 CARS AND THE MAN WAS GOING TO SELL THEM. EMMA CONSTERDINE 6YRS WE WENT TO BRADENSTOKE STORE IN MRS GILBER'S CAR .MRS GILBERT COULD TOUCH THE CEILING BECAUSE IT IS VERY OLD . MATTHEW OSBOURNE 6YRS. WE SAW A THATCHER PUTTING WILLOW STICKS ONTO A ROOF TO STOP THE BIRDS FROM PECKING THE STRAW OFF THE THATCHED ROOF MICHAEL MAREK 6YRS.
